Client&#39;s machine time will affect your serverside data only if you send it directly via GET\POST requests and then pass as a parameter for DateTime object. 
Otherwise php script gets date, time and timezone from the server where it runs.

Most of the webservers are setup to UTC timezone (which is also a good practice for storing datetime records in DB), but I would recommend to check if that it is true for yours.

    &lt;?php

    // This var contains only server time
    $serverDataTime = new \DateTime();
    
    try {
    	$userTimeZone = new \DateTimeZone($_POST[&#39;timezone_from_client&#39;]);
    	// this one depends on what was received from the client
    	$userDateTime = new \DateTime( $_POST[&#39;date_time_from_client&#39;], $userTimeZone );
    } catch ( Exception $e ) {
    	// wrong input
    }

Manual: [PHP DateTime][1]


  [1]: https://www.php.net/manual/en/datetime.construct.php

