answers.body_markdown:
`setForm` is a setter function returned from `useState` which should take your new state. In your case, you are trying to assign the property `selectedItems` to this function:

    const handleChange = (selectedItems) =&gt; {
      setForm.selectedItems=selectedItems;
    };

You should instead call the function with your updated state:

    const handleChange = selectedItems =&gt; {
      setForm({ ...form, selectedItems });
    };

